5470.String: On the happiest day of her life, Haru's world is suddenly torn asunder when the Vacuuum devours her family. In shock, she swears revenge and in so doing unleashes her Soul Energy. Haru wields her sword with a fiery blend of guilt and atonement.

5471.String: Fun is Erwin's greatest motivator – and that goes for his Soul Energy as well. Eyes wide open, he was the only one to walk into the Vacuuum voluntarily. Even the apocalypse cannot wipe that broad grin off his cheerful face.

5472.String: Lily derives her Soul Energy from her smouldering madness. A terrifying encounter with a beast from the Vacuuum drove her over the edge. She tends to act the delicate, well-bred society girl, but behind the mask...

5473.String: Jin is extremely noble and selfless, and his unerring passion feeds his Soul Energy. With complete disregard for his own well-being, he fights injustice wherever he sees it, for the good of humanity. Is that even possible in the ruins of this world...?

5474.String: Sensitive Stella grew up around abusive and hostile people. Her Soul Energy manifests this sorrow. You wouldn't know it to look at those rosy little cheeks, but her Howling Guitar speaks volumes.

5475.String: Deep down inside Iris boils a rage at a world gone awry which unleashes her Soul Energy. She perceives even herself with the same wrath and frustration, vowing to improve herself. But all she hears is a scornful echo which fills her with a livid emptiness.

5800.String: <font color='#FFFFFF'><font size="30">TIP。</font>You can purchase standard Armor from <font color='#00ff9c'>Zyte</font> in districts.

5801.String: <font color='#FFFFFF'><font size="30">TIP。</font> You can buy standard consumables from <font color='#00ff9c'>Yomi</font> in every district.

5802.String: <font color='#FFFFFF'><font size="30">TIP。</font> In shops, you can <font color='#00D8FF'>[Repair]</font> the durability of your weapons or <font color='#00D8FF'>[Dismantle]</font> your Items.

5803.String: <font color='#FFFFFF'><font size="30">TIP。</font> The more frequently you visit functional NPCs, the quicker your <font color='#00D8FF'>[Client Level]</font> will increase. When your Client Lv. increases with an NPC, their services improve.

5804.String: <font color='#FFFFFF'><font size="30">TIP。</font> At <font color='#00ff9c'>Trisha's</font> you can <font color='#00D8FF'>[Upgrade]</font> or <font color='#00D8FF'>[Refine]</font> weapons and equipment.

5805.String: <font color='#FFFFFF'><font size="30">TIP。</font> If you want to get more out of your Items, you can <font color='#00D8FF'>upgrade</font> them or <font color='#00D8FF'>dismantle</font> them to obtain upgrade or crafting materials.

5806.String: <font color='#FFFFFF'><font size="30">TIP。</font> At <font color='#B2EBF4'>[Janice]</font> you can <font color='#00D8FF'>[Craft]</font> weapons, Armor and costume Items.

5807.String: <font color='#FFFFFF'><font size="30">TIP。</font> <font color='#00ff9c'>H.E.M.S</font> Use the H.E.M.S facility to send messages to other Players.

5808.String: <font color='#FFFFFF'><font size="30">TIP。</font> <font color='#00ff9c'>Oden</font> is the one to entrust your <font color='#00D8FF'>Items</font> to for storage in every district.

5809.String: <font color='#FFFFFF'><font size="30">TIP。</font> Use the <font color='#00ff9c'>Mini map</font> to check your own position, that of an <font color='#00D8FF'>NPC</font> and see where <font color='#00D8FF'>Mazes</font> are.

5810.String: <font color='#FFFFFF'><font size="30">TIP。</font> For details on Progress, press the hotkey <font color='#00ff9c'>L</font> and see <font color='#00D8FF'>[Achievements] [Sharing Rate]</font>.

5811.String: <font color='#FFFFFF'><font size="30">TIP。</font> Depending on your progress, you will find your rewards in <font color='#00D8FF'>Progress</font> <font color='#00ff9c'>[L]</font>.

5813.String: <font color='#FFFFFF'><font size="30">TIP。</font> There are some passive <font color='#00D8FF'>Akashic Record</font> that will trigger automatically in combat if you have added them to your slots.

5814.String: <font color='#FFFFFF'><font size="30">TIP。</font> New quests can be recognized by an <font color='#fff94a'><font size="30">!</font></font> mark and Completed quests with an <font color='#fff94a'><font size="30">?</font></font> mark.

5815.String: <font color='#FFFFFF'><font size="30">TIP。</font> You can see the quests you accepted in <font color='#00D8FF'>Quest Info</font> at the right or by pressing the hotkey <font color='#00ff9c'>[J]</font> to view Quest Info.

5816.String: <font color='#FFFFFF'><font size="30">TIP。</font> To bind hotkeys, press <font color='#00ff9c'>ESC</font>. You can change the settings any time in <font color='#00D8FF'>[Settings]</font>.

5817.String: <font color='#FFFFFF'><font size="30">TIP。</font> The community has lots of features for <font color='#00D8FF'>[Friend]</font> for you to use.

5818.String: <font color='#FFFFFF'><font size="30"> TIP。</font> To use an <font color='#00D8FF'>[Skill] [Akashic Record]</font>, open the Akashic menu with the <font color='#00ff9c'>[K] [;]</font> hotkey or via the UI, and add it to your Akashic Record.

5819.String: <font color='#FFFFFF'><font size="30">TIP。</font> Rely on your <font color='#00D8FF'>Skill tree</font> for powerful effects in combat.

5820.String: <font color='#FFFFFF'><font size="30">TIP。</font> Invest in <font color='#00D8FF'>passive Skills</font> to enhance your active Skills.

5821.String: <font color='#FFFFFF'><font size="30">TIP。</font> You can check your own Progress in the <font color='#00D8FF'>Info window</font> at the bottom left.

5822.String: <font color='#FFFFFF'><font size="30">TIP。</font><font color='#00D8FF'>Titles</font> can be set to how you like to have them displayed or applied.

5823.String: <font color='#FFFFFF'><font size="30">TIP。</font> You get rewards for <font color='#00D8FF'>Maze Progress</font> and <font color='#00D8FF'>District Progress</font>.

5824.String: <font color='#FFFFFF'><font size="30">TIP。</font> Progress in Mazes of a particular zone effect the superordinate <font color='#00D8FF'>Maze progress</font>.

5825.String: <font color='#FFFFFF'><font size="30">TIP。</font> When entering a Maze, use <font color='#00D8FF'>[Auto Team Search]</font> to assemble your Team automatically.

5826.String: <font color='#FFFFFF'><font size="30">TIP。</font> You can change your Character Info in the <font color='#00D8FF'>profile</font>.

5827.String: <font color='#FFFFFF'><font size="30">TIP。</font> Press <font color='#00ff9c'>[ALT]</font> to switch to mouse mode.

5828.String: <font color='#FFFFFF'><font size="30">TIP。</font> Once you reach level 55, the </font><font color='#00ff9c'>[Rank]</font> matters.

5829.String: <font color='#FFFFFF'><font size="30">TIP。</font> If a channel is too full, use the <font color='#00D8FF'>switch channel</font> feature in the upper part of the mini map.

5830.String: <font color='#FFFFFF'><font size="30">TIP。</font> You obtain B.P (<font color='#00ff9c'>BP</font>) for Bucker in <font color='#00D8FF'>District 6</font> and <font color='#00D8FF'>Steel Graves</font>.

5831.String: <font color='#FFFFFF'><font size="30">TIP。</font> You can buy special PvP Items in the <font color='#00ff9c'>BP shop</font> in <font color='#00D8FF'>Maze 6</font>.

5832.String: <font color='#FFFFFF'><font size="30">TIP。</font> Open <font color='#00D8FF'>Quest Info</font> to see <font color='#00ff9c'>[Daily Mission]</font>.

5833.String: <font color='#FFFFFF'><font size="30">TIP。</font> Doing <font color='#00D8FF'>daily quests</font> earns you Gruton Gold, which you can spend in the <font color='#00ff9c'>Gruton Coin</font>.

5834.String: <font color='#FFFFFF'><font size="30">TIP。</font> Random </font><font color='#00D8FF'>[Hidden Quests] (HQ)</font> appear within the Mazes.

5835.String: <font color='#FFFFFF'><font size="30">TIP。</font> When in Mazes, call upon </font> <font color='#00D8FF'>[Supporter]</font> you acquire as the game progresses. Occasionally, you will receive unexpected aid.

5836.String: <font color='#FFFFFF'><font size="30">TIP。</font> Register an </font><font color='#00D8FF'>Orb</font> with <font color='#00ff9c'>Eo</font> so friends can use the Orb for their allies.

5837.String: <font color='#FFFFFF'><font size="30">TIP。</font> If it gets too lonely or difficult all by your self, use </font><font color='#00D8FF'>Team Search ‘N'</font> or </font><font color='#00D8FF'>Community [O]</font> to find Players to join you.

5838.String: <font color='#FFFFFF'><font size="30">TIP。</font></font> Found a <font color='#00D8FF'>League</font> or join an existing </font><font color='#00D8FF'>League</font> to make new friends.

5839.String: <font color='#FFFFFF'><font size="30">TIP。</font> From Lv.10 you can have a place to call <font color='#00D8FF'>[My Room]</font>.

5840.String: <font color='#FFFFFF'><font size="30">TIP。</font> Sometimes a remnant of the old world will appear in the Mazes, known as a <font color='#00D8FF'>Memorial</font>.

5841.String: <font color='#FFFFFF'><font size="30">TIP。</font> Click on the golden icon at the top right to access <font color='#00D8FF'>[Help]</font>, which has details on a lot of topics.

5842.String: <font color='#FFFFFF'><font size="30">TIP。</font> Entering a Maze consumes <font color='#00D8FF'>[FP]</font>.

5843.String: <font color='#FFFFFF'><font size="30">TIP。</font> You can upgrade your <font color='#00D8FF'>Skills</font> and <font color='#00D8FF'>Skill</font> to suit your playing style. New effects can erase and new functions can be added.

5844.String: <font color='#FFFFFF'><font size="30">TIP。</font> For favorable combat, it is essential to watch out for <font color='#00D8FF'>[Traumas]</font>.

5845.String: <font color='#FFFFFF'><font size="30">TIP。</font> Occasionally you will encounter enemies who have <font color='#00D8FF'>[Super Armor]</font>. If you destroy their Super Armor, the enemy will falter.

5846.String: <font color='#FFFFFF'><font size="30">TIP。</font> You can attack with a single mouse click when <font color='#00D8FF'>[Dash]</font> and <font color='#00D8FF'>[Jump]</font>.

5847.String: <font color='#FFFFFF'><font size="30">TIP。</font> If you attack an enemy while they are in the air, you can deal additional damage.

5848.String: <font color='#FFFFFF'><font size="30">TIP。</font> If you complete certain quests in the Mazes, you will receive <font color='#00D8FF'>Soul Vapor</font> and can use the <font color='#00ff9c'>[Break Skill]</font>.

5849.String: <font color='#FFFFFF'><font size="30">TIP。</font> <font color='#00D8FF'>Grutons</font> appear in the Mazes at random.

5850.String: <font color='#FFFFFF'><font size="30">TIP。</font> Collect different <font color='#00D8FF'>Items</font> as you progress through the game to grow stronger.

5851.String: <font color='#FFFFFF'><font size="30">TIP。</font> If you have Items with sockets you can attach an <font color='#00D8FF'>Familiar</font> to them.

5852.String: <font color='#FFFFFF'><font size="30">TIP。</font> If you have costume Items with sockets, you can attach <font color='#00D8FF'>brooches</font> to add Skills to them.

5853.String: <font color='#FFFFFF'><font size="30">TIP。</font> When you defeat enemies, they drop <font color='#00D8FF'>Ether</font>. Ether is required for <font color='#00ff9c'>upgrading</font>.

5857.String: <font color='#FFFFFF'><font size="30">TIP。</font> In District 6 you can use the<font color='#00D8FF'>Starry Forest League's chopper</font> to cross safely.

5861.String: <font color='#FFFFFF'><font size="30">TIP。</font> You can enter the combat training zone <font color='#00D8FF'>Steel Graves</font> any time you like once you have unlocked it in Candus City.

5866.String: <font color='#FFFFFF'><font size="30">TIP。</font> The more frequently you visit functional NPCs, the quicker your <font color='#00D8FF'>[Client Lv.]</font> will increase. When your Client Lv. increases with an NPC, their services improve.

5867.String: <font color='#FFFFFF'><font size="30">TIP。</font> At <font color='#00ff9c'>[Trisha]</font> you can <font color='#00D8FF'>upgrade</font> or <font color='#00D8FF'>[Upgrade] [Exchange]</font> weapons and equipment.

5868.String: <font color='#FFFFFF'><font size="30">TIP。</font> If you want to get more out of your Items, you can <font color='#00D8FF'>upgrade</font> them or <font color='#00D8FF'>Dismantle</font> them to obtain upgrade or crafting materials.

5869.String: <font color='#FFFFFF'><font size="30">TIP。</font> At <font color='#B2EBF4'>[Janice]</font> you can <font color='#00D8FF'>[Craft]</font> weapons, Armor and costume Items.

5870.String: <font color='#FFFFFF'><font size="30">TIP。</font> <font color='#00ff9c'>H.E.M.S</font> Use the H.E.M.S facility to send messages to other Players.

5871.String: <font color='#FFFFFF'><font size="30">TIP。</font> <font color='#00ff9c'>Oden</font> is the one to entrust your <font color='#00D8FF'>Items</font> to for storage in every district.

5872.String: <font color='#FFFFFF'><font size="30">TIP。</font> Use the <font color='#00ff9c'>Mini map</font> to check your own position, that of an <font color='#00D8FF'>NPC</font> and see where <font color='#00D8FF'>Mazes</font> are.

9996.String: [The Primal] is only permitted for use as a raid Maze in the most difficult mode for Forces, i.e. 8-Player Teams permitted. Stop the world's downfall and be victorious in Primal Park!

10031.String:
A boot camp where hopefuls are tested before joining the Starry Forest League.
They run easy to tough combat simulations.

10032.String: A building site in Rocco Town. Construction has halted. The NED Company was attempting to extract the Soul Energy hidden underground beneath this construction site.

10033.String:
The abandoned 7th street in Rocco Town.
Defend it against the assault by Mad Edgar's Mannequins and stop the self-destructing Giant Mannequin. The city must be saved!

10034.String: The crazy Vessi joker known as "Pierrot Edgar" has created his own circus troupe at the national hospital and now threatens the inhabitants.

10041.String: A top secret laboratory where the NED Company was carrying out clandestine reSearch. Currently the facility is off-limits due to a mysterious accident.

10042.String:
A motorway near Candus City that the Vessi Rapid Flame Forces have captured.
Currently the Starry Forest League is planning a joint operation with the NED Company to retake the zone.

10043.String:
The NED Company's western branch, located at Candus City centre. This zone is currently occupied by the Rapid Flame forces.
The Energy is lead by the Green Wind Witch, Witch of the Rending Winds.

10044.String: A gigantic transport aircraft that NED Company has provided for the retreat from Candus City. The aircraft is being prepared for take-off in the secret subterranean hangar beneath Candus City.

10051.String: A small suburb in the outskirts of Grace City. The Rapid Flame cash Inventory's new weapon has reduced this little suburb to smoking rubble. The Starry Forest League has dispatched a scout squad to discover the nature of this new weapon.

10052.String: The area along the front line. This is where open war rages between the Starry Forest League and the Rapid Flame cash Inventory. Forced onto the defensive, the SFL intends to establish a base for the rebuilding project by recapturing the area.

10053.String: A subterranean sewage tunnel that extends across Grace City. The Starry Forest League is planning a surprise attack on the Rapid Flame through this area and preparing the operation.

10054.String: A secret military camp of the NED Company. The Starry Forest League discovered the secret agreement between the NED Company and the Rapid Flame, and is now preparing an operation to neutralise this area.

10061.String: The central control system of Ruin Fortress, monitored by the high-powered AI Lucy. The Starry Forest League is attempting to retake this area to grant respite to the Near SoulWorker Search op.

10062.String: The location of the Buster Cores, the main power source of Ruin Fortress. First of all, the deactivated Buster Cores need to be reactivated to restore power inside Ruin Fortress.

10063.String: A secret laboratory inside of Ruin Fortress. Digger, the massive bore, is trying to execute something hidden in the bedrock. The Starry Forest League launches the operation to stop Digger.

10064.String: A tracking operation is launched to catch Abel and Sion, who have fled to the Ark Ship: a gargantuan ship currently being built in secret in the outskirts of Ruin Fortress.

10081.String:
The Mist of Madness that Mad Edgar had sprayed still hung over Rocco Town, lurking.
Defend R Square against the major assault by Mad Edgar's Mannequins.

10089.String:
Mad Edgar is preparing the final parade, which is to be the culmination of the attack on Rocco Town. 
But this is where the brutal festival will end.

10090.String: As the self-destruct button is activated, the last escape route from the N-102 laboratory opens.  Defeat the terrifying Beholder blocking the way and return safely.

10091.String:
The evil greed of the NED Company led to forbidden Experiments on live human subjects.
Stop the SoulWorker production project and grant peace to the victims.

10092.String:
Another way to reach the Acheron, where the strongest robots have slept, waiting to be completed.
Break through the robots who have Awaken from their long sleep, and bring the operation to a successful close.

10097.String:
The remaining Soul Junk horde and Mad Edgar's Mannequin army are up to their evil tricks in Rocco Town again.
Smothered in thick fog and smoke, Rocco Town must be defended to the last.

13005.String: The verification failed due to system maintenance.

15000.String:
A testing ground for the combat Skills of Starry Forest League soldiers. 
Robots modified for testing await the SFL combatants.

15001.String: Miriam rushed to the drill site, where work had been halted to rescue a child. But the sudden Soul Junk assault cut her off.

15002.String: Soul Junk, Dread roams the construction site. He is the culprit who destroyed Warren's hospital and terrorized Rocco Town with an epidemic alert. Kill him before he spreads the plague.

15003.String:
Heeding Miriam's request, you have just reached the drill site.
Survivors stranded here must be found and brought to safety.

15004.String: Ryu went to the place where awakeners was sighted by himself. Who knows what's going to happen, you've got to help him quickly.

15005.String:
The Clown's invitation points to the deserted road of the main square.
What gifts await you there?

15006.String:
Countless mannequins crowd the roads around the main square.
A road that was once teeming with people and life
has turned into a road of soulless dolls.

15007.String: To stop Big Puppet's advance, a helicopter will be needed that happens to belong to the NED Company. The mannequins have got to be stopped before they destroy the helicopter.

15008.String:
Operation [The Shield].
A dangerous operation in which Big Puppet is lured into the defence wall and its self destruct triggered. The operation must not fail.

15009.String:
The mannequin forces has resurfaced.
The scout squad sent to investigate them hasn't returned, either. You sense a sinister aura.

15010.String:
Humans who have become mannequins, a tower that emits a sinister aura, and mannequins labouring tirelessly...
What are the mannequins building the tower for?

15011.String:
It was the tower that turned the people into mannequins.
Benjamin orders the tower's destruction, before it can wreak even more havoc.

15012.String:
The talking mannequin, codename: Jack The King
The only way to escape this situation is to defeat Jack The King.

15013.String:
Finally, the Blue Flame Clown has been tracked down.
He is in an abandoned hospital near Rocco Town. Find the vanguard and pursue the Blue Flame Clown.

15014.String:
According to your Info you need a special badge to reach the Blue Flame Clown. 
You can find the badge on the mannequin servants inside the hospital.

15015.String: You reached the ward where the Blue Clown is based. The badge got you through the magnetic field, and you finally reached the Clown.

15016.String:
The Blue Flame Clown, Mad Edgar, fled and challenged you to a Outputdown in the circus tent on the hospital roof. 
The final fight begins. He must be stopped, whatever the cost.

15017.String: You have scarcely arrived in the new town and you aren't given a moment's rest. The next operation is already underway: Clear out the Soul Junks on the coastal road to secure the supply route to Candus City.

15018.String:
The reports from NED mercenaries of another powerful Soul Junk on the coastal road have been confirmed. 
They say he is in a constant rage...

15019.String: Recently, the coastal roads have experienced inexplicable earthquakes. There is a risk that this might cause flyovers and buildings to collapse. We must find out what is causing the earthquakes and solve the problem.

15020.String: Yet another pack of Soul Junks has appeared. To defend Candus City, Lieutenant Colonel Aaron gives orders to eliminate the Soul Junks and detonate the last remaining supply route: the coastal tunnel.

15021.String:
Given permission by the NED Company, you have reached the subterranean sewage tunnels.
You nearly choke on the stench.
It feels like something really is alive here.

15022.String: Several parts of the city now stink like the sewers. It is evident that the source of the abominable stench must lie in the sewer system.

15023.String: The NED Company has assembled a large squad of mercenaries and reSearchers and sent them into the sewers. Brooke, who grew suspicious of their activities, ordered them surveilled.

15024.String: The arrival of the Junk Knight shocks the entire Starry Forest League. To hold the NED Company accountable, Brooke orders a sample procured from the Junk Knight.

15025.String:
You have learned that a NED Company dropship has crashed in a nearby residence. 
We must learn what was on board.

15026.String:
The entire residence has turned into a Soul Junk's lair.
There is a highly contagious Soul Junk here. It should be killed before it gets outside.

15027.String: Ralph says it is believed that Catherine is somewhere deep inside the residence. Go further into the residence find Catherine.

15028.String:
Supposedly, the Soul Junk Arachness who abducted Catherine has hidden deep below the residence. 
We must find Catherine soon.

15029.String: It is said that the only antidote to Catherine's infection from Vacuum Vein is located within the NED Company's laboratory. But the lab has already become a cave teeming with Soul Junks.

15030.String: The second lab was a Soul Junk's lair as well. Who knows what made these places change so drastically, but the priority is to find the antidote for Catherine.

15031.String:
Racked with guilt over losing Catherine, Victor entered the depths of the laboratory alone to find the antidote.
He must be found before a Soul Junk gets him.

15032.String: Henry says that to be effective, the antidote requires secretions from Beholder, and he also gave orders to demolish the laboratory.

15033.String: Right after returning from Rocco Town, a massive army of Soul Junks attacked Candus City. To rescue the people, the control unit for the air raid shelter has got to be opened.

15034.String: An inordinate number of Soul Junks were discovered inside the air raid shelter and on the way to the transport airship. They have to be killed first to protect people from being attacked.

15035.String: Most of the inhabitants had been taken to safety. Only we and Catherine remained. It was at that very moment we discovered a mass of Soul Junks heading toward the transporter we were supposed to board.

15036.String:
After leaving Candus City behind, our flight began in earnest. 
But the pack of Soul Junks attacked the airship with tenacity. Everyone was extremely concerned.

15037.String: Although there was barely enough time to pursue Henry as it was, orders came down to bring back Vessi. The orders must be followed, for now.

15038.String: The Rapid Flame Vessi which lusts for power. The Rapid Flame's assault squad is planning to invade Grace City via the motorway and awaits its opportunity.

15039.String: A vehicle that Henry supposedly used has been found. Plenty of questions remain, but first we have got to save him before he is attacked by the Vessi.

15040.String: No trace of Henry, target of the revenge, but [Scar], leader of the Rapid Flame cash Inventory, has Outputn himself on the motorway. To learn of Henry's location, Sukkarak must be stopped.

15041.String: An urgent message has arrived stating that the Rapid Flame raid squad took the NED Company office compSedurin after Henry penetrated the NED HQ. We have got to rescue him, unfortunately.

15042.String: Since the Rapid Flame captured the building, the power supply inside the NED Company has been erratic.

15043.String: To restore power to the NED Company, it has to be activated by hand from inside the building. Evidently, the Rapid Flame has the key.

15044.String: To obtain evidence of Henry's deeds in Candus City, all data from the security box inside the NED Company needs to be copied.

15045.String: This operation is about stopping the Rapid Flame's attack squad before they reach the second motorway. To activate Wolf Cry, secure the shooting position for the Mountain Troll.

15046.String: Operation [Wolf Cry]'s target is to launch the high frequency rocket F-ARIA to neutralise Queen Garura, the attack squad's mainstay.

15047.String: The Mountain Troll cannot move until F-ARIA is launched. Together with Kane Barrel, a SoulWorker of the Starry Forest League, the Rapid Flame attack squad must be stopped.

15048.String: When his beloved mount Queen Garura is wounded, Falcon, commander of the Rapid Flame attack squad appears. Isn't it glorious when an enemy so rarely seen in person Outputs himself?

15049.String: In a deserted place where silence smothers the roads, the cold rain in Deaf Town only spurs the ominous sense of foreboding.

15050.String: Deaf Town, a little town near Grace City, is home to many people. With the war far off, Deaf Town has retained economic independence.

15051.String: One can only hope this foreboding will be gone with the rain. There is no time! The SoulPath markers have to be set up to discover how Soul Energy flows through Deaf Town.

15052.String: The ominous sense of foreboding became reality, after all. What are they after, doing such terrible things...? Well, we've got to Search for survivors first.

15053.String: And so it is that the alliance stands between Henry and the Rapid Flame cash Inventory. Henry must be stopped and finally brought to justice for his unspeakable deeds.

15054.String: The place believed to be the Rapid Flame headquarters turned out to be a trap set by the NED Company working hand in glove with the Rapid Flame.

15055.String: The NED Company's malignant stratagem placed Grace City in a perilous position from which it could not escape. We cannot let them die like that!

15056.String: The Rapid Flame's kill squad is preventing the relief squad from carrying out the rescue op. If we are to save even one person, the enemies preventing it must be eliminated.

15057.String: There are indications the NED Company hacked the military's Indra satellite. We need to trace the hack to find its source.

15058.String: The trail leads to a place near the mountains, in the outskirts of Grace City. It's time to let them feel a punishing blade.

15059.String: To locate Henry and Rauper, the interference signal that is crippling the military satellite has to be shut off.

15060.String: Indra's scan of the facility interior Outputs two life forms, probably Henry and Rauper. Finally the time has come to avenge them.

15061.String:
A virtual training simulator the Starry Forest League has developed exclusively for SoulWorkers. 
Enemies registered in the database are set up as holograms or robots to simulate a realistic combat situation. The simulator consumes a lot of power and cannot be used very often.

15062.String:
A zone that has been laid to waste by the Vacuum.
Soul Junks appear here constantly. The Starry Forest League has marked the area off limits to civilians.

15063.String:
The sudden appearance of the mysterious distortion unleashed countless mannequins onto Earth.
Nobody knows where they come from or how they managed to invade our world.
All we know is that they are powerful and hostile.

16100.String:
An upside down world.
Stunned people.
Unbelievable stories.
Everything I knew has come crashing down.
What... what's going to become of me?

16200.String:
I awake from a 15-year-long slumber to find all hell has broken loose.
Monsters roam and humans have supernatural powers.
I find myself in the world I always dreamed of.
It's all so unsettling, so different... so thrilling.

16300.String:
A world which has no room for the things we took for granted...
Well...
I never took anything for granted.
I fought hard and bitterly for everything by the sweat of my brow.
That won't change now... not even in this world.

16400.String:
They say a lot has changed in the last 15 years.
They say that survival is all that matters in today's world.
Huh... what can I say?
Survival has always been all that mattered to me.

16500.String:
When I opened my eyes, I was told I had been asleep for 15 years.
Do they think I'm a bear that hibernates?
They keep talking about things I don't understand. Plus, I'm starving, and nobody's giving me anything to eat...
Hm... at least I'm with everyone else instead of all by myself.
I guess that's something.

16600.String:
The world I knew is gone.
Everything seems to strange and unpleasant. I don't want to stay here a minute longer.
But I've got to face it.
This is the world I'm going to be living in.
I've got to persevere and tough it out.

33000.String:
Hello.
May I introduce myself? My name is Mad Edgar, and I am a humble clown who is always in Search of the best of all Outputs in this turbulent world.
I presume you are quite surprised about this message coming out of the blue.
However, I really wanted to tell you just how deeply I admire your strength.
Your power has been the most impressive spectacle I've ever seen in my short life.
Glorious yet unassuming, beautiful yet ugly, soothing yet destructive.
I have pondered long and hard on how to express my explosive feelings
Now I've decided to send you a little gift.
It is a token of my reverence for you and your strength. Please do not decline it.
You will find the gift in the place you humans call the shopping Maze.
I sincerely hope... that you like it.
- Yours respectfully, Mad Edgar -

33001.String:
I can sense that we are getting closer to each other.
I do not doubt that we shall meet soon.
Yet isn't it likewise true that the longer we wait, the happier the occasion will be?
I have prepared a little game for dramatic effect.
Your current strength will not permit you to get past the place in front of the room where I am located.
I have taken care to ensure that you can get past that place easily with the badge my servants carry.
Please hurry.
Before my heart, which longs for you so, is filled with hate.
-Yours respectfully, Mad Edgar-

33002.String:
- Report: Amaryllis -

1. Added Soul Energy immunity to subject SJ-DS-01 Condition: Unstable.

2. Observed parasitism in subject SJ-DS-01. Subject infects human Soul Energy hosts.
Infected hosts lose their Soul Energy permanently. Symptoms: Skin like plaster.
The host merely serves as a source of food for SJ-DS-01 now.

3. Valid name for SJ-DS-01: Dignity Snatcher. Additional finding: The Dignity Snatcher accumulates and stores the Soul Energy it absorbs. However, the mass of Soul Energy detected far exceeds the maximum capacity of a host, i.e. a human. The mass we are investigating currently exceeds the capacity of all our instruments.

33003.String:
- Report: Tempest -
1. The fuselage is an apparatus assembled with utmost precision. Based on our data on Rapid Flame technology, we can conclude that we do not have the means to create a Rapid Flame of our own with our methods. We hypothesise that an external force was used to produce it.

2. The weapon fires highly concentrated Desire Energy.

3. The Armor includes a special wire and a crane which can lift 700 kg.
We estimate the Armor's attack damage to be devastating.

4. The special wire is capable of storing and transmitting Soul Energy.

33004.String:
On a gloomy day.
The child's fury was predictable. It's difficult to comprehend people who call this phenomena a disaster. The truth is, we have sinned and the time has come to atone for our sins. As the representative of all other children, the time has come to hand out just punishment. Even if it is called revenge, I will accept it as atonement.

On a snowy day.
Foolish people have caused the child to fall into a deep sleep again. They took comfort in the thought that it would all be over once the child was asleep. The foolish belief that the NED Company would save us makes me mad with rage. They will bury everyone who knows the truth. As though nothing had ever happened.

On a clear day.
After it was decided to mark this place off-limits, everyone but the management board was left behind in this hell. It won't be long before everyone is dead. Indeed. We have sinned. It is only just to die like this. I do not fear what we face.

33005.String:
Model name: NS_EX_008
Name: Cleany

1. As the name suggests, this is a cleaner robot. Measures the Soul Energy in subjects. Suitable for sorting rubbish and Searching for lost Items.

2. Currently in sleep mode because it is out of energy. If it is supplied with energy 3 times, it will reawaken from stasis and begin to move by itself.
(It will take about 24 hours until it starts to move.)

3. If the core is lost or destroyed: If an amplifier is found and inserted into the core position as a substitute core, The core can be reactivated.
(However, it must have at least 1% propulsion.)

I would like to thank the people who made it this far with the help of the notes.
The Ruin Fortress harbours no sinners, except... the [People] here.
The same goes for this robot.
I firmly believe that you, who have come all this way merely in answer to the words [HELP ME], will look after this child as well. I need your help. 
And I need Dusty. May your path be blessed with happiness.

40817.String: I fell asleep after watching a scary movie with monsters and wild animals and weird men last night.

40818.String: But then, in the dream, I was standing in a dark alley all alone!

40826.String: But after that, wide-eyed monsters and spikey monsters came running to me and it scared me.
